Windows
------------
Install Intel RealSense SDK 2.0:
    Download and install the latest Intel RealSense SDK 2.0 from Intel RealSense GitHub releases.
    During installation, make sure to select the option to install development headers and libraries.

Install CMake:
    Download and install CMake from the CMake website.

Install OpenGL and GLFW:
    Download the latest GLFW binaries from GLFW's website.
    Place the include and lib folders in your project directory or configure your environment variables.

Install Visual Studio:
    Install Visual Studio with C++ development tools.
    Configure your project to link with the librealsense2.lib, glfw3.lib, and opengl32.lib libraries.

Set up the Project:
    Ensure that your project includes the path to Intel RealSense headers and links to the RealSense, OpenGL, and GLFW libraries.





MacOS
------------
Install Homebrew:
    Open Terminal and install Homebrew if you havenâ€™t already:
    /bin/bash -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/HEAD/install.sh)"

Install Intel RealSense SDK 2.0:
    Run the following command to install the RealSense SDK:
    brew install librealsense

Install CMake:
    Install CMake via Homebrew:
    brew install cmake

Install GLFW:
    Install GLFW using Homebrew:
    brew install glfw

Install OpenGL:
    MacOS comes with OpenGL by default, so additional OpenGL setup is typically unnecessary.

Build the Project:
    Create and navigate to a build directory:
    mkdir build && cd build

Generate the makefiles and build:
    cmake .. && make -j5
